by House of Alfbad » Sat Mar 27, 2021 7:41 am

Despite its federal nature, Zuamaland's legislature is unicameral, which sounds a bit weird because bicameralism is essentially an aspect of federalism, meant to give states a say in legislature as much as the people. Moreso, its system seems like it is built to be inefficient and haphazard: Presidents serve for five-year terms but only once (Which means it's both too long and too short for anyone to create a long-term plan) while legislators serve on two-year terms but can renew their terms four time (which, again, means it's too short to do anything and they'll be trying to campaign pretty much the moment they take their seat). Then again... this might be by design, given their semi-direct democratic nature.
